variables.value: I'm sure the thief's hiding close by.\nThere should be clues nearby too.
Good luck with your investigation!
Thanks kindly, Ace Detective! I'm sentencing these little guys\nto community service—as our official store mascots!
What? That's none of your business! I'm not telling you anything!
Hillview Terrace is just up this road, right?\nMy boss is hopeless with maps.
Hopping on the No. 9 West Bus was our mistake.\nTook us way out into the mountains...
It's so calm and relaxing along the coast.\nI came by car today. It was a surprisingly easy drive.
I took my boss' advice, and brought castella from Harborfront Bakery\nto that important meeting I had lined up. It went down great!
Coastal houses need renovations more often\nbecause of the salty, humid sea air.\n...Eh, don't mind me. Just sharing some fun facts.
Must be nice, working for the Football Association...\nNot that I dislike my job or anything, though.
I caught a glimpse of a <LST:KIDO> helicopter\nwhile on a business trip in Tokyo.\nThat deep-green bodywork, the bright red logo... So cool.
I heard President <LST:SAKURAZAKI> is coming back to Japan soon.\nWonder if he's got business to take care of here?
Apparently the <LST:SAKURAZAKI>s' manor is around here.\nIt's less fancy than I'd expected...
I was so impressed by the driver handling those hilly roads,\nI didn't even realize I was on the wrong bus until it was too late, heh!
Many families around here have lived in <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> for generations.\nThere's probably a fair bit of demand for home renovations.
There's nary a soul in Nagasaki who can resist Harborfront's castella!\nHave a slice ready, and most things sort themselves out.
Hey, sharing is caring! Knowledge should be traded and shared.\nWhich is fitting for a trading port town like Nagasaki.
Youth football's always been full of dreams.\nIt's one of the top forms of entertainment—\nand there's a whole lot of money in it, too.
If you asked me to choose between Tristar\nor <LST:KIDO>'s Heavy Industries...\nWell, I'm from Nagasaki. I'd have to go with Tristar.
So <FLC:SAKURAZAKI> from the <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> football club\nis President <LST:SAKURAZAKI>'s son? Wow, I had no idea.
Where... are we?
Did we take\na wrong turn?
We definitely did.\nI'm sure of it.
<LST:SAKURAZAKI>'s manor is\naround here, right?
We finally made it.
That turned into\nquite the trip.
Well, at least I know\nthe route now.
That'll make things\neasier next time!
Should be somewhere\naround here.
Glad we made it\nin one piece.
Told you\nyou could rely on me!
Heh heh, that you did!
I'm so glad\nit all worked out...
Nice work!
It's all thanks to\nyour advice!
Ah, well, not entirely.
Hmm... I see...
No rush. You'll get the\nhang of it.
There's lots to learn.\nI can do it, though!
That's the spirit!
The stadium was\nabsolutely buzzing!
You managed to\ncatch a game, eh?
Yeah... Every player\nlooked ambitious.
Ah, youth football...\nA fine thing indeed.
Company helicopters\nare pretty sweet, eh?
Yeah, they've a sense of\nadventure to 'em.
Especially those <LST:KIDO>'s\nHeavy Industries models.
Gotta love 'em.
You hear about\nPresident <LST:SAKURAZAKI>...?
Huh? What about him?
He's returning to Japan,\napparently.
That's kind of rare,\nright?
I hope the beach opens to the public soon.\nI'm itching to see if I can swim all the way to that island!
<MNT:NAGUMOHARA> has plenty of baseball fields, but only one pool.\nWe're always vying for pool time with the water polo club...\nIt's such a hassle.
Those water polo guys...
Tch, what a pain.
I hope the beach opens soon; I can't swim in peace at the school pool.\nThe water polo club always get in the way of my practice...
The football club's new pitch is super nice.\nGuess the swimming club will have to show its stuff,\nand push for another pool!
Speed is everything!
I'm gonna be the best\nin the whole club.
The fastest swimmer gets to be club captain.\nI've gotta prove myself next tournament, and take that spot!
It's awesome that we've got such a beautiful ocean right by us.\nI'd love to paint the sea view someday.
Not now though...\nMaybe later...
Ah! But,\nit's so pretty...!
Hydrangeas change color even after they've bloomed.\nHm. I wonder which shade would look best in a painting...?
I like painting, but never joined the art club.\nThey're hardcore. They'll do anything for their art...
You've crossed the seas\nso many times.
Such an\ninteresting flower...
Apparently, hydrangeas originated in Japan.\nThen new varieties bred in Europe were imported back here.
<FLC:BIJIMA>, the head of the art club, is a troublemaker.\nBut oh so passionate about art. That's why people let his antics slide.
The shopping district's always packed.\nGetting a <FUL:UMIBOZUMAN>burger there's such a headache!\nGood thing they sell 'em here too, right?
I'd be a surefire winner in a Hungry <FUL:UMIBOZUMAN>burger eating contest.\nThat <FUL:KAMEO> might give me competition, though!
The nice old man at <FUL:TANAKA> Mart gives me a discount sometimes.\nHe's such a generous soul!
I wanted my friend up in Tohoku to try a Hungry <FUL:UMIBOZUMAN>burger too.\nSo I had Bluewave Express deliver three whole boxes!
<FUL:UMIBOZUMAN>burgers are the best!\nI've gotta get the old Northbright guys to try them too!
That candy's\na great choice!
Oh really?
Yeah, it lasts forever.
Guess it won't melt\nin my pocket then!
Has it always been this hot?
Feels like it's getting\nhotter every year...
I need a cold drink,\nmaybe...
I always end up buying\nsomething or another.
Ooh, tough choice...
You can't go wrong\nwith the classics.
They all look so good...
Simple is best!
The student council's\nkinda scary...
They've even got\nbig burly bodyguards.
Like <FLC:YAJIMA>\nfrom the judo club...
Intimidating, right?
The football club's\npretty impressive.
Yeah. They're the\ntalk of the town.
Did you hear about\nthe rugby club, though?
About <FLC:USHIJIMA>, you mean?
Oh, this ice cream...
It's the kind <FLC:TABE>\nthe commentator loves!
It's gone viral\nacross social media.
Huh. So you can\nbuy it here now, too.
Hey, about gym class\nthe other day...
The group class, with the\nNorthbright students?
Yep, it was intense.
Yeah! That football\nmatch was a blast!
You hear about\nSouthcrest High?
They're changing their\nyear divisions, right?
Maybe they'll have to\nretake entrance exams?
Who knows...
I wonder when swim\nclasses will start...
Eh, I swim like\na brick, though...
But post-swim ice cream\ngoes so hard!
Can't argue with that!
I kinda want to\ntransfer to Alpine.
In Hokkaido?
Yeah, where it's\nfresh and cool!
Man, you really can't\ntake the heat, eh?
It's already the finals,\nhuh...
So soon!
Did you see\nthat show on TV?
Yeah, the one\nabout Raimon, right?
It's still so warm, even after sundown.\nHard to believe it was winter not so long ago.
It's still only spring, but I'm sweating buckets in this heat.\nDays like this really make you crave ice cream.
Huh? You show up, and I instantly start shivering...\nIt was warm just a moment ago!
I can never choose between a cup or a cone.\nCups are better at catching melting ice cream.\nBut cones are so crispy, so tasty...
Speak of the devil! You're in that famous football club, right?\nMaybe I'll jump on board and sign up too.
Speaking of, <FLC:TABE>'s intense commentary is the best.\nHe really gets you fired up something fierce!
<FLC:SORAMIYA> is usually cheerful and easygoing,\nbut it's like a switch flips on when he's on the football pitch.\nLike he's a whole other person.
I always end up falling asleep after swim class.\nThose naps are the best.
I bet Hokkaido's cool all year round...\nMaybe I should actually transfer to Alpine Junior High.
Summer's almost here.\nTime really flies...
I bought too much candy. My allowance for this month is almost dry!\nI just can't stop snacking, though...
Cold treats sure hit the spot when your brain's fried from studying.\nMaybe I'll grab some shaved ice today.
I bet you never have to worry about your allowance, <FLC:SAKURAZAKI>.\nYou can probably buy all the snacks you want... I'm kind of jealous.
I'm really craving a Chilling Ice Cream.\nMaybe I'll head down to the port.\nYou can't get that delicate, sweet taste anywhere else!
<FLC:USHIJIMA> charges like a freight train but feels out of place in rugby.\nNow he's looking for a place to truly show his skills.
They've got that ice cream <FLC:TABE> raves about in stock here.\nIt's in short supply in the city, but you can find it all over out here.
I wonder if anyone from Northbright shares my love for sweets.\nWouldn't it be funny if someone like <FLC:JINNAI> had a secret sweet tooth?
Aw, the chocolate I had in my pocket's melted.\nSummer's here, alright...
Rabbit Food's in Hokkaido, too!\nTheir candies are the best. They really lift your spirits!
I heard the Raimon Junior High cafeteria sells lightning-shaped cakes!\nI kinda want to try one.
What are we looking\nfor again?
A four-leaf clover!
I'll help.
There aren't any here.\nLet's just go.
I'm telling you,\nwe're gonna find one!
Where could they be...?
We're almost there!
It's Megane Bridge!
I'm so excited!
Chinatown too!
Ooh, maybe we'll\nget to see that park.
The night view's\nsupposed to be amazing...
Huh?\nYou can ride a bike?
Wow, that's awesome!
What, you guys can't?
I mean, I don't even\nhave my own bike.
Me neither!
Oh, really?
Yeahhh, rides!
I wonder what other\nfun stuff they have?
I can't wait to go!
I'm gonna snap\ntons of pictures!
The flower fields are\nso beautiful in spring.
And in winter, it's all\nabout the lights.
I'm so hyped\nfor the factory tour!
Ooh, that's where they\nmake marble soap.
It's so sparkly...
And see-through, too!
I wonder how it's made.
I can't wait\nto find out!
Where are you going\nthis summer break?
Marina Resort!
Wow, lucky!
Wait, can you even swim?
W-Well...
Why not just bring\na floatie?
Hey, can you whistle\nwith your fingers?
Yep, sure can!
Whoa!\nThat's awesome!
Did you practice it?
N-Not really...
That's even cooler!
I wanna go to\n<MNT:NAGUMOHARA>.
Huh? Why?
To focus on\nyour studies?
Nope.\nI want to play football!
Oh, the football club!
I'm gonna join\ntheir club too!
We're headed for all kinds of places on this field trip!\nHey, have you ever seen Megane Bridge?
We're going to Cupid's Carnival soon!\nThe flower gardens are super pretty, I hear.\nBut the rides have gotta come first, right?
I can't wait for our field trip!\nWe're going to Chinatown for lunch!
I'll wear those fluffy ears to Cupid's Carnival!\nYeah, I'll pretend I'm Flammy the Cat. It'll be a blast!
I hear that park's popular in the evenings.\nThe view at night's something special, it's super popular!
I'm looking up info on Cupid's Carnival right now.\nThe amusement park's massive. As big as Naniwa Land, even!
Can't believe I actually\nreeled in a halibut.
I'm happy for you.
I'd like to go\nriver fishin', too.
I'll show ya the ropes\nnext time!
A sashimi knife, huh...
Get a good one,\nit's worth it.
I haven't a clue\nhow to use 'em though.
Not to worry!\nI'll teach you!
My, they've\nbloomed beautifully.
Now, what should I\nplant next, heh heh...
Oh. I caught a puffer...
Hey, don't toss\nit back in.
What, you're really\ngonna eat it?
There's a way to\ncook it, you see!
What a haul!
The fish were bitin'\nlike crazy.
We're in for\na feast tonight!
It'll be fun\ncookin' all this up.
Flying fish broth's\nreally something special.
Now I'm startin'\nto crave it.
How about some\nGoto noodles for dinner?
Now that's a fine idea!
Nothing's biting, huh...
The sea's a fickle\nmistress sometimes.
But I guess that's\npart of the fun.
That's the spirit!
I'm headin' to\nAwaji Island.
Oh? Goin' on a trip, eh?
Yeah, I've a friend\nwho lives out that way.
Sounds nice.
Been thinkin' what snack\nI should get my grandkid.
Dried sardines maybe?
Ah, there's an idea.
They're jam-packed\nwith nutrition.
He first got me into fishin'. Now I'm so hooked, I go every day.\nOne time I landed a whole load of halibut. That was a day to remember!
I can hardly cook at all, let alone prepare raw fish.\nBut I live by the sea. Might as well learn how to prepare sashimi!
I think I'll try my hand at growing fruit. I did some research,\nand it seems loquats are pretty resistant to the sea breeze.
I always toss 'em back too... they're too much trouble to prepare.\nBut maybe it's worth the challenge, eh?
Nagasaki's a fisherman's dream, there are so many species to catch.\nA keen angler could never get bored in a place like this.
Noodles with rich broth hits the spot, every time!\nI think I'll mosey on over to Wellspring Noodles tonight.
They call it "getting skunked"\nwhen you don't catch the fish you're after. It's a pain!\nBut planning just how to reel it in is a thrill in itself.
A pal of mine's an onion farmer on Awaji Island.\nI'm plannin' to go visit him soon. It's been a while.
Kanto folk love 'em, or so I hear.\nFunny how tastes change by region.\nWouldn't have known if a city kid hadn't pointed it out.
It's actually a kind of flatfish.\nThey're easy enough to catch, and quite tasty, so they're real popular.
I'm headin' to the port tomorrow.\nThe fish out there are a little different to those by the beach.
Preparing a catch you've just reeled in is part of the fun.\nA splash of sweet soy sauce really brings out the flavor.
Gotta cut off the poisonous bits, but they taste pretty good.\nKinda like mean-lookin' folks—\nhard to approach, but decent once you get to know 'em.
I love fishing, so I'm stoked to see my buddies get into it.\nYou should get your pals to join your hobbies, too.
When the haul's a big 'un, nothing beats sashimi or simmered fish.\nPair it with a little booze, and you're all set!
Y'know, some people drink the broth on its own!\nFlying fish, often used to make it, are common around the Goto Islands.
Guess I'll head\nto G-Mart.
It's a bit of a trek,\nthough...
If I get skunked, I swing by a sushi place to treat myself.\nNagasaki's finest fish, prepped by a skilled chef—\nain't a bad way to end the day!
They say there's a mighty fine waterfall pool on Awaji Island.\nWonder what kinda fish might be livin' in there!
Gotta eat your sardines each day to grow tall!\nThey're packed with calcium, y'know.
Oho! This calls for\na proper welcome.
It's been too long,\nmy friend!
My brother writes for a football magazine. He's dropping by soon.\nI'll get some inside stories on the Spring Cup out of him!
There's this local grade school team that's super talented!\nTheir captain, <FLC:KUDAIRA>, is a shooting prodigy.
People always focus on\nthe baseball club...
The other clubs\ndeserve attention too.
<MNT:NAGUMOHARA> is always putting the baseball club on a pedestal.\nMy child's club is doing pretty well too, y'know!
I always knew <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>'s football club would make a comeback.\nI've believed in them for years.
<MNT:NAGUMOHARA>\nand West Manor...
It's a well-known\nrivalry around here.
Their feud runs deep.\nEven the principals see each other as rivals, did you know that?
<MNT:NAGUMOHARA> is a big school, a safe choice for a merger.\nThey've got plenty of outstanding students, my kid included.
I heard rumors about\nFauxshore Junior High...
Something about\ntheir striker, right?
The word is, Crosswind-Fauxshore has two powerful strikers.\nAccording to my kid, anyway.
I've actually seen <FUL:TSUNAMI> in the flesh.\nBet you're jealous, eh?
You young'uns probably don't know, but back in the day,\npeople said Royal Academy would destroy any school that lost a match.
I saw this coming from a mile away.\nI knew the football club would make it to the finals.
I bet the Seagull FC kids will end up playing in the Football Frontier\nonce they're in junior high.
Northbright did\ntheir best, too...
Who would've thought...
It's a shame Northbright's run in the Spring Cup was cut short.\nWho knew <FUL:ENDO>'s son would be that strong...?
Hey, is it true that the <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> football club's back?\nWell I'll be cheering 'em on for sure!
It's so moving...
Seeing them\ngive it their all.
My kid tells me the <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> football club's\nbeen training late into the evening, eh? I'm cheering you on!
Northbright's football team is pretty strong, right?\nSo <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> might have a real shot\nat winning the Football Frontier now.
They actually withdrew from the regional finals!\n...Well, I guess that's typical of Mary Times.
Royal Academy went undefeated for forty years back in the day...\nGoing up against such a historic school is no small feat!
Just imagine, they form a team—\nand are up against the great Raimon in less than a year!\nThat alone is a huge deal!
They put even junior\nhigh teams to shame.
They must have\na good manager.
They might even make\na tournament someday.
I hope they keep it up\nin junior high too.
What was that\nargument about...?
I tried asking, but,\nit's still a mystery.
Well, that figures.
So is everything\nokay now?
Northbright\nand <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>...?
Yeah. They're merging,\nso I hear.
I didn't see\nthat coming!
Yeah, came\nout of nowhere.
Mary Times,\nhuh...
Isn't their manager\n<FLA:TSUNAMI>?
Fitting!\nJust like old times.
It feels like déjà vu.
About Royal Academy...
What about them?
People used to say...
Pretty terrifying, huh?
That <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>, eh...
To think they'd banned\nfootball at one point!
Things change fast, huh.
Even the PTA\nwas shocked!
Good evening!
Watch out for traffic,\nalright?
Ahh.\nAnother peaceful day!
What a nice sea breeze.
Big waves today...
Be careful on the roads\nat night, okay?
Yep, no issues here!
Some calm waves\nwe've got today, eh?
Hmm... Those\nBack Alley Kickers...
They've kept their\nnoses clean, as of late.
Ah. It's them again...
Huh? They play\nfootball now?
The Back Alley\nKickers. Hmm.
Guess they've\nturned over a new leaf.
Do you watch InaTube? Word on the street is,\na popular InaTube streamer lives in <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>.
Maybe I'll start streaming, too.\nI could stream, um... All the cats around <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>?
This InaTuber I watch keeps talking football.\nKinda like the <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> crew...\nTotal coincidence. Probably.
Streaming sounds fun, but finding content's rough.\nCome to think of it...\nthe newspaper club posting daily is kinda nuts.
"<FUL:MAN-TAICHO>'s <FUL:MANMANTV>!"\nSo catchy. I can't get that Platinum InaTuber's intro out of my head!
Masked InaTubers are so cool...\nTheir identity's a secret, so your imagination goes wild!
That <FLC:MANBE> in our class is kinda plain and unassuming. You know?\nBut for some reason, I always catch myself glancing at him.
Just as expected.
You reeled that\nin nicely!
A fine black bream!
You sure know your way\naround a fishing rod!
A new personal best!
That was a tough fight!
This beach is a real\nhidden gem.
The fish are really\nbiting today, eh!
There's a great fishing\nspot over in Saga.
Really? Whereabouts?
A place called\nTwinford Village.
I see. Interesting...
Kumamoto has some\nace fishing spots too.
Really? Kumamoto, huh?
Yeah, over near\nOrchid Academy.
You mean that\ngirls' school?
So, I went to Fukuoka,\nand...
And? What happened?
I ran into a gang\nof troublemakers...
Th-That sounds scary.
What a haul!
So much herring!
I'd say it's about\nsashimi-o'-clock.
Tempura sounds good too!
Wanna go reel in\nsome grunts?
Sounds like a plan!
They're in season,\nafter all.
Yeah, they'll be nice\nand fatty by now.
The new students this\nyear are something else.
They're making\nwaves already.
Even the seniors are talking about you guys.\nStanding out too much might hurt your academic record, though...
The juniors are\nplaying football, huh?
Guess that means the\nfootball club's back?
The changes to the school were a shock.\nEveryone freaked out. I didn't even mind the old green building!
<FLA:IBUTO>\nis so strict.
Grandkids are made\nto be spoiled, y'know!
Are you from <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> like little <FST:RAIKA>?\nHer grandpa's tasked her with odd training routines for ages now.
Your grandkids' health:\nnothing matters more!
I just want\nto see them smile.
<FLC:IBUTO> can be strict with his granddaughter <FST:RAIKA>, sure.\nBut deep down, I know he just wants to dote on her.
So she's into football?
She can do anything\nshe puts her mind to.
I heard little <FST:RAIKA>'s got into football now.\nShe's a quick learner, so I'm sure she'll do just fine.
I've lived here\na long time, you see.
Everyone feels like\na grandchild to me!
<FST:RAIKA>'s not fighting with her teammates, is she?\nI've known her since she was little...\nCan't help but fuss like she's my own grandkid.
<FUL:KAMEO>...?
Oh! He's been into\nfootball lately, right?
Hey, you go to <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> Junior High, right?\nAre you friends with <FUL:KAMEO>?\nHis mom's always been a huge help to me.
<FLA:OTOHINA>\nis so amazing.
I've gotta keep up\nwith my lessons.
Ever since I joined Aquacore Fitness, my speed's way up.\nSome creep tried hitting on me the other day—I outran him easy!
I hope <FST:KAMEO>'s doing OK.
I'm worried about him.
I wonder if <FST:KAMEO>'s sleeping alright in Tokyo.\nHis mother was really worried for him, too...
I saw <FST:KAMEO>\nplaying football.
He was really\ngiving it his all.
I had no idea <FST:KAMEO> could play like that!\nHe must be training really hard.
